        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Ok here is what I did and it seemed to fix me - I downgraded to the 4.0.1 firmware and then went to my router and did a reset - this is done by holding in the reset button until the RED WAN light comes on.  </P><P>This erases ALL the router settings.</P><P>I then resetup my router to point out to the internet and everything has seemed to work fine.</P><P><BR>- CK<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
